Reasoning: 
1. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper deals with designing a distributed algorithm for a group of communicating agents, which falls under the scope of multi-agent systems.
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The problem of tracking time-varying reference signals can be seen as a control problem, and the paper discusses the design of algorithms to achieve this objective.
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with designing a distributed algorithm for consensus, which falls under the scope of distributed computing.
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the communication capabilities of the agents, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the design of algorithms for achieving consensus, which can be seen as a problem in artificial intelligence.
